cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.HC, cs.IR, cs.LG. 

The paper presents an online platform for story understanding, which involves natural language processing and argumentation. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The platform also includes social features, such as community repository and collaborative editing, which suggest a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the platform involves web service infrastructure and integration with other systems, which may relate to information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG).
